{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-poicephalus-rueppellii", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-poicephalus-rueppellii", "name": "Rüppell's parrot", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "bird-r-ppell-s-parrot-07267054", "name": "Rüppell's parrot", "englishName": "Rüppell's parrot", "latinName": "Poicephalus rueppellii", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "Rüppell's parrot (Poicephalus rueppellii) or Rueppell's parrot, is a bird that is endemic to southwestern Africa from central Namibia to southwest Angola. It lives in savanna where there are trees or in dry woodland. It is more common near streams or rivers. The name commemorates the German naturalist and explorer Eduard Rüppell. Description Rüppell's parrot is 22–25 cm (8.7–9.8 in) long and weighs 121–156 g (4.3–5.5 oz). It has an overall black color. Both adult male and female birds have some yellow feathers on the leading edge of the wings, and yellow feathers covering their upper legs; in immature birds, the yellow is dull or missing. It is sexually dimorphic; adult female birds have blue feathers on the lower back and the rump, while male birds lose this blue feather coloration as they become mature. Diet Ruppell's parrot eats mainly seeds, flowers, leaves, arthropods, and bark. It has been found that during the rainy seasons they prefer to eat flowers and insects. Consistently they eat Terminalia pruniodies and occasionally they also eat fruit, preferring softer more tender ones. Breeding Rüppell's parrot nests in tree cavities. The eggs are white and there are usually three or four in a clutch. The female incubates the eggs for about 28 days and the chicks leave the nest about 68 days after hatching. Status It is a protected species, listed on CITES appendix II. References Further reading External links Rüppell's parrot – Species text in The Atlas of Southern African Birds.", "shortSummary": "Rüppell's parrot (Poicephalus rueppellii) or Rueppell's parrot, is a bird that is endemic to southwestern Africa from central Namibia to so…", "habitats": ["稀树草原"], "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/R%C3%BCppells_parrot-5275_-_Flickr_-_Ragnhild_%26_Neil_Crawford.jpg/960px-R%C3%BCppells_parrot-5275_-_Flickr_-_Ragnhild_%26_Neil_Crawford.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-poicephalus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-poicephalus-rueppellii", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-poicephalus", "species": "taxonomy-species-poicephalus-rueppellii"}, "expandable": true, "x": -67.39, "y": 88.41, "z": -392.51}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-poicephalus", "name": "Poicephalus", "latinName": "Poicephalus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Poicephalus（Poicephalus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联10种鸟类，如Brown-necked parrot、Cape parrot、Red-fronted parrot等10种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 10, "x": -600.75, "y": 79.03, "z": 61.49}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-poicephalus-rueppellii", "name": "Rüppell's parrot", "latinName": "Poicephalus rueppellii", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Rüppell's parrot（Poicephalus rueppellii）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Rüppell's parrot。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -67.39, "y": 88.41, "z": -375.59}], "links": [{"key": "bird-r-ppell-s-parrot-07267054__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-poicephalus-rueppellii", "source": "bird-r-ppell-s-parrot-07267054", "target": "taxonomy-species-poicephalus-rueppellii", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-poicephalus-rueppellii__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-poicephalus", "source"